cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper focuses on image denoising and high-level vision tasks, which are both related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes deep learning solutions for these tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in computer vision, and may also suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods using visual quality metrics, which may suggest that it also belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
